  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to examine the effectiveness of a psychotherapy (non-medication)&#xD;
      treatment, Brief Cognitive Behavioral Therapy for Suicide Prevention, in reducing suicide&#xD;
      ideation and attempts for people with physical disabilities.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
